cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on security in mobile ad hoc networks, which falls under the networking and internet architecture sub-category. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a security solution to prevent blackhole attacks, which is a type of routing attack. This falls under the cryptography and security sub-category. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed solution to prevent blackhole attacks in a MANET, which falls under the distributed computing sub-category. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the impact of blackhole attacks on the overall performance of AODV in a MANET, which falls under the social and information networks sub-category. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new protocol (DPRAODV) to prevent blackhole attacks, which involves designing and implementing new algorithms. This falls under the data structures and algorithms sub-category.
